  "derivation_layer": {
    "source_latex": "% BEGIN TZP DERIVATION LAYER\n\\tzpsection{Derivation Layer}\n\\paragraph{Primary Equation.}\n\\begin{equation}\n\\eta(\\omega)\n=\n\\omega^{-\\beta}\ne^{-\\omega/\\omega_0}.\n\\end{equation}\n\n\\paragraph{Primary Derivation.}\nLet $\\omega$ be a frequency variable and let $\\omega_0$ be the characteristic cutoff frequency determined by the Trawin base unit.\n\nA scale-sensitive spectral law begins with a power term:\n\n\\begin{equation}\n\\omega^{-\\beta},\n\\end{equation}\n\nwhere $\\beta$ controls low-frequency or scale-weighted behavior.\n\nTo suppress high-frequency divergence, introduce the exponential cutoff:\n\n\\begin{equation}\ne^{-\\omega/\\omega_0}.\n\\end{equation}\n\nMultiplying the two factors gives the TZP-weighted spectral density index:\n\n\\begin{equation}\n\\boxed{\n\\eta(\\omega)\n=\n\\omega^{-\\beta}\ne^{-\\omega/\\omega_0}.\n}\n\\end{equation}\n\n\\paragraph{Interpretation.}\n$\\eta(\\omega)$ weights frequency contributions by combining power-law scaling with exponential cutoff suppression.\n% END TZP DERIVATION LAYER"
  },
